<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1436,986,1766]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,289,1634,1659]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Biology</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson, 1895:" authorityYear="2156" box="[303,521,1634,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Meteorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abscissus">
<emphasis box="[303,521,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Meteorus abscissus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded as a parasitoid of several 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[938,1073,1634,1658]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Lepidoptera</taxonomicName>
families, in particular 
<taxonomicName box="[1325,1432,1634,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Arctiidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[151,296,1670,1694]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Geometridae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Yu et al. 2005)" baseAuthorityName="Yu" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[349,647,1670,1694]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Noctuidae (
<bibRefCitation author="Yu, D. S. &amp; Achterberg, C. van &amp; Braconidae &amp; Horstmann, K. &amp; Ichneumonidae" box="[478,639,1670,1694]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" refId="ref60475" refString="Yu, D. S., Achterberg, C. van. (Braconidae) &amp; Horstmann, K. (Ichneumonidae). 2005. World Ichneumonoidea 2004 - Taxonomy, Biology, Morphology and Distribution. DVD / CD. Taxapad. Vancouver, Canada. www. taxapad. com." type="book" year="2005">Yu et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Old host records might be erroneous due to the difficulties in properly separating some intermediate specimens from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wesmael" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[685,877,1706,1730]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Meteorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchricornis">
<emphasis box="[685,877,1706,1730]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">M. pulchricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We found 
<specimenCount box="[1015,1156,1706,1730]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="generic">4 specimens</specimenCount>
within the SMTP. They were caught in late July and early August in arid, exposed environments.
</paragraph>
